onsidering how to ensure coverage for dynamic-access classes, meaning each should have its own dedicated Java test file, like ClassUtilsTest. I'm thinking about using implemented interfaces with a private interface, and checking if a class can be instantiated with a no-arg constructor. Since the nested class is package-private, it can still be public static final. There’s also the point about constructors: a default constructor for a public nested class seems to align with public access. It should work out seamlessly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring ServiceLoader and interfaces**\\n\\nI'm reflecting on using ServiceLoader for a nested interface and how it involves loading the class with the class loader. I'm aware that ServiceLoader.load utilizes the thread context class loader (TCCL) and will search for resources. There’s a concern with non-public service interfaces, but if the service class is a public nested interface, we shouldn’t have to throw exceptions if there's no service configuration. Additionally, I'm noting that if metadata isn't generated under native conditions, exceptions from method.invoke could lead to assertion failures. It’s quite a puzzle!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UW13mxvITOuhCjT15w4acj4l|fc_0c4e761191b5223e016a020b75049c819faebfd5ebc9530487", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/11.14.1/src/test/java/flyway/ClassUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage flyway;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.util.ClassUtils;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClassUtilsTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void detectsPresentClassesWithTheProvidedClassLoader() {\n        ClassLoader classLoader = ClassUtilsTest.class.getClassLoader();\n\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.isPresent(PresentType.class.getName(), classLoader)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.isPresent(\"flyway.DoesNotExist\", classLoader)).isFalse();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void detectsWhetherServiceImplementationIsPresent() {\n        ClassLoader classLoader = ClassUtilsTest.class.getClassLoader();\n\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.isImplementationPresent(UnregisteredService.class.getName(), classLoader)).isFalse();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsConcreteImplementationsAndVerifiesTheyCanBeConstructed() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader classLoader = ClassUtilsTest.class.getClassLoader();\n\n        Class<? extends GreetingService> loadedClass = ClassUtils.loadClass(\n                GreetingService.class,\n                DefaultGreetingService.class.getName(),\n                classLoader);\n\n        assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(DefaultGreetingService.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsPublicStaticStringFieldsByName() {\n        ClassLoader classLoader = ClassUtilsTest.class.getClassLoader();\n\n        String value = ClassUtils.getStaticFieldValue(StaticFieldHolder.class.getName(), \"VALUE\", classLoader);\n\n        assertThat(value).isEqualTo(\"static-value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsAndWritesDeclaredFields() {\n        MutableConfiguration configuration = new MutableConfiguration(\"initial\");\n\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.getFieldValue(configuration, \"name\")).isEqualTo(\"initial\");\n\n        ClassUtils.setFieldValue(configuration, \"name\", \"updated\");\n\n        assertThat(configuration.getName()).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.getFieldValue(configuration, \"name\")).isEqualTo(\"updated\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void listsGettableFieldsFromClassHierarchy() {\n        ExtendedLoggingConfiguration configuration = new ExtendedLoggingConfiguration();\n\n        List<String> fields = ClassUtils.getGettableField(configuration, \"flyway.\");\n\n        assertThat(fields).contains(\"flyway.name\", \"flyway.description\");\n        assertThat(fields).doesNotContain(\"flyway.class\", \"flyway.secret\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void readsGettableFieldValuesFromClassHierarchy() {\n        ExtendedLoggingConfiguration configuration = new ExtendedLoggingConfiguration();\n\n        Map<String, String> fieldValues = ClassUtils.getGettableFieldValues(configuration, \"flyway.\");\n\n        assertThat(fieldValues).containsEntry(\"flyway.name\", \"production\")\n                .containsEntry(\"flyway.description\", \"primary database\")\n                .doesNotContainKey(\"flyway.secret\");\n    }\n\n    public interface UnregisteredService {\n    }\n\n    public interface GreetingService {\n    }\n\n    public static final class PresentType {\n    }\n\n    public static final class DefaultGreetingService implements GreetingService {\n        public DefaultGreetingService() {\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class StaticFieldHolder {\n        public static final String VALUE = \"static-value\";\n    }\n\n    public static class MutableConfiguration {\n        private String name;\n\n        MutableConfiguration(String name) {\n            this.name = name;\n        }\n\n        public String getName() {\n            return name;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ExtendedLoggingConfiguration extends MutableConfiguration {\n        ExtendedLoggingConfiguration() {\n            super(\"production\");\n        }\n\n        public String getDescription() {\n            return \"primary database\";\n        }\n\n        @ClassUtils.DoNotMapForLogging\n        public String getSecret() {\n            return \"hidden\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3126, "output": 2064, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32326, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "ca